commitResults.messageTitle: Echo the commands entered by user with way to exit program
commitResults.messageBody:
Echo the commands entered by user. Exit program when the user types
the command "bye".

commitResults.messageTitle: Add ability to store text and display when requested
commitResults.messageBody:
Add ability to store text in an array and display it back when the user
requests for it by typing "list"

commitResults.messageTitle: Add the ability to mark tasks as done/not done
commitResults.messageBody: Add the ability to mark tasks as done/not done. Make class for tasks.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add support for tracking three types of tasks
commitResults.messageBody:
Add support for tracking three types of tasks:
1. ToDos: tasks without any date/time attached to
2. Deadlines: tasks that need to be done before a specific date/time
3. Events: tasks that start at a specific date/time and ends at a
specific date/time

commitResults.messageTitle: Test using the I/O redirection technique
commitResults.messageBody:
Create test cases and use the input/output redirection technique to
semi-automate the testing of Lebron.
